<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Non-owning SymbolStringPool entry pointer. Instances are comparable with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="238"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SymbolStringPtr instances and guaranteed to have the same hash, but do not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><Highlight kind="comment">/// affect the ref-count of the pooled string (and are therefore cheaper to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><Highlight kind="comment">/// copy).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="241"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><Highlight kind="comment">/// NonOwningSymbolStringPtrs are silently invalidated if the pool entry&#39;s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ref-count drops to zero, so they should only be used in contexts where a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><Highlight kind="comment">/// corresponding SymbolStringPtr is known to exist (which will guarantee that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the ref-count stays above zero). E.g. in a graph where nodes are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><Highlight kind="comment">/// represented by SymbolStringPtrs the edges can be represented by pairs of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><Highlight kind="comment">/// NonOwningSymbolStringPtrs and this will make the introduction of deletion</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of edges cheaper.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/nonowningsymbolstringptr"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/nonowningsymbolstringptr/#a1b07b73c4b416133b5a40b5d275f1fdb">NonOwningSymbolStringPtr</a> : </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">public</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolstringptrbase/#a334e27918886db7a1a9e3ac95e34d569">SymbolStringPtrBase</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">friend</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/densemapinfo">DenseMapInfo</a>&lt;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc">orc</a>::<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/nonowningsymbolstringptr/#a1b07b73c4b416133b5a40b5d275f1fdb">NonOwningSymbolStringPtr</a>&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
